        "shortName": "SPAS-12",
        "description": "The SPAS-12 (Special Purpose Automatic Shotgun, 12 gauge) was designed in the late 70's as a combat shotgun for use by global military and police forces before later being superseded by the SPAS-15 in 2000. The SPAS was designed with both pump action, intended for use with low-pressure rounds like less-lethals or tear gas, and semi auto, intended for use with normal slugs or buckshot rounds. Manufactured by Franchi"
